"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-06-23-Olympic-Day-China-at-the-Summer-Olympics-1uEWdahQeXe-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  CGTN  Copied  Olympic Day on June 23 marks the founding of the International Olympic Committee in Paris in 1894. The People's Republic of China began its Olympic journey in 1952 at the Helsinki Summer Games. Since then, China has made a significant impact in sports, including hosting the 2008 Beijing Summer Olympics and the 2022 Beijing Winter Olympics.  With the 2024 Paris Summer Olympics just over a month away, let us explore China's achievements in the previous Summer Olympic events. Over the years, China has participated in 11 Summer Olympics.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"